The paper is about evaluating neural networks on various types of random graphs, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the structural and numerical properties of the graphs, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions functional resting state fMRI networks, which could be related to signal processing (cs.SI) and statistical learning (cs.SD).
